  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Accuracy of predicting histology with EC</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year</time_frame>
    <description>Polyps will be visualized in white-light and the location and size will be noted. Afterwards, electronic chromoendoscopy will be used to visualize and enhance the mucosal vascular pattern and the mucosal surface pattern morphology of the polyp. The endoscopist will then make a real time assessment of each polyp according to size, shape, Paris classification and surface characteristics including pit pattern and mucosal vascular pattern morphology, colour, and type of depression. Further, a level of confidence (high or low) will be made for the real time histology prediction. Finally, all polyps will be removed using standard techniques and processed for pathological evaluation and real time and histological results will be compared.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
